# knowledge-kernel Skill

**A Knowledge Kernel that provides deterministic grounding for AI agents.**

**Definition (2026-07-10):** knowledge-kernel is a **deterministic, reproducible and auditable factual substrate** for AI agents. It stores verified facts, the evidence supporting them, their relationships and their recency, so multiple agents can reason from the same observable reality.

**The three emergent properties (form a reinforcing chain):**
```
Reproducibility → Auditability → Determinism
```
Every fact carries `provenance.discovered_by + discovery_method + discovery_run` so any observation can be re-executed. If it can be reproduced, it can be audited. If it can be audited, agents arrive at the same fact — deterministically.

`[references/greenfield-rebuild.md](references/greenfield-rebuild.md)` — 8 operational rules (organized as: Honestidad 1-3, Gobernanza 4-6, Temporalidad 7-8), 4-layer epistemology (Reality → Evidence → Facts → Grounded Reasoning), anti-patterns from v1, dataset v2 state (36 entities, DQS=100%, FFR=100%, valid=True).

**Core positioning:** "LLMs infer; knowledge-kernel provides a shared, evidence-backed source of truth so multiple agents can reason consistently from the same verifiable reality."

