## Project Structure & Governance

**Principle: One Responsibility, One Canonical Home, One Source of Truth.**

The repository enforces a strict separation of concerns through its directory structure:

```
knowledge-kernel/
├── cmdb/              # Core API (models, rules, query, impact, validator, **engine**)
├── tests/             # SINGLE home for all tests (no parallel suites)
├── docs/              # ALL documentation (architecture, philosophy, patterns)
├── examples/          # Canonical examples (5 YAMLs, one per kind)
├── integrations/      # Integration wrappers (Hermes, future: Langflow, OpenWebUI)
│   └── hermes/
│       ├── tools/     # Hermes tool wrappers (cmdb_*.py, kpi.py, **cmdb_clear_cache**)
│       └── SKILL.md   # Skill manifest
├── scripts/           # CLI wrappers (general-purpose tooling only)
├── data/              # EMPTY (gitignored) — production dataset lives externally
├── pyproject.toml
└── README.md
```

**Layering principle:** `tools → cmdb.api → engine → YAML`. Tools are adapters; engine is infrastructure core. Never invert.

**Cleanup date:** 2026-07-11 (commit `14b8fcf`) — consolidated structure, eliminated redundancy.

### Key Decisions

| Directory | Purpose | What Lives Here |
